item.title: Did AOC remove her pronouns from X bio? Here's what happened
item.description: "AOC removing the pronouns from her bio is a hell of a vibe shift," one social media user posted. X's community notes, however, suggested that AOC did not remove her pronouns after the election results, she might have done this months ago but came to the notice now. Republican leader Marjorie Taylor Greene said AOC needs to explain her action "after shoving gender lies and insane ideology down people’s throats for years, why has she removed her pronouns?".
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump rules out JP Morgan's Jamie Dimon for administration role
item.description: Despite earlier speculation of Jamie Dimon being considered for the Treasury Secretary position, US President-elect Donald Trump confirmed that Dimon will not be joining his administration. Dimon, CEO of JPMorgan Chase, had previously indicated his unwillingness to accept a government role.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Whoopi Goldberg claims she was denied her birthday treats because of politics, bakery responds
item.description: Whoopi Goldberg alleged that a New York City bakery, later identified as Holtermann's Bakery, refused to bake her birthday desserts due to her political views. The bakery denied the claim, citing boiler problems. "They said that their ovens had gone down, all kinds of stuff, but folks went and got them anyway,” Goldberg explained, “which is why I'm not telling you who made them," Goldberg said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Elon Musk's college photo goes viral after Trump appoints him to lead DOGE
item.description: A vintage photo of Elon Musk from his college days resurfaced on social media, sparking widespread reactions. The photo emerged following the announcement of Musk co-leading the 'Department of Government Efficiency' (DOGE) in the upcoming Trump administration. Musk himself acknowledged the photo, expressing amazement at his journey.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Nikki Haley says she knows Trump's game: 'He knew I have no interest'
item.description: Haley said she told Witkoff that no truce was needed and she was not revolting against Trump but was supporting him and in exchange she did not want anything. “I told him at the time there was no truce needed, that Trump had my support. There was no issue on my end. At that point, he was like, ‘What do you want? Tell me what you want. Is there anything you want?’ I said, ‘There’s nothing I want.’”
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: British Hindus and Indians raise concerns over Oxford Union Kashmir debate speakers' alleged link to terrorism
item.description: INSIGHT UK, a British Indian social movement, has formally objected to the Oxford Union's decision to host a debate on Kashmiri independence. Their concern stems from the invited speakers, Muzzammil Ayyub Thakur and Zafar Khan, who allegedly have ties to extremist groups.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Finally, Prince Harry may return to the Royal Family as his biggest enemy is retiring
item.description: Tina Brown wrote that Harry and Alderton had a personal enmity and that dominated Alderton's advice to King Charles to not welcome Harry back to the royal fold. The replacement of Alderton by a figure without any personal animosity with Harry could "create a new, friendlier path for negotiations with Harry". In his memoir Spare, Harry christened Alderton as "The Wasp" -- such is the extent of their enmity.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Matt Gaetz college roommate' rumor resurfaces on X after Trump names him as attorney general
item.description: Apart from a sex trafficking case, Matt Gaetz was linked to the unnatural death of his roommate at Florida State University but the case was ruled as a suicide. Now that he has been named as the attorney general, the rumor resurfaced on social media. Republican leaders are certain that Gaetz won't get confirmed by the Senate. Gaetz needs a Senate majority to become the attorney general.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Police find up to 20 human skulls in New Mexico residence, link one to missing woman
item.description: Police in New Mexico made a chilling discovery of up to 20 human skulls in a home in Jal, potentially linked to the 2019 disappearance of Angela McManes. The investigation began when a resident reported a disturbing encounter with Cecil Villanueva, who allegedly discarded bags containing human bones.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 2 Israeli airstrikes hit Syria's capital and suburb, killing 15 people, Syrian state media says
From Elon Musk to Tulsi Gabbard: One fun fact about each member of Team Trump 2024
item.description: Imagine if Ray Clay, the voice that ignited the Chicago arena, were to announce the newest Team Trump 2024 line-up. Close your eyes and let Sirius by The Alan Parsons Project echo in the background. It’s 2024, and the air is thick with MAGA fever. Each pick is making Washington pundits go redder. There’s the former news anchor who is now head of Pentagon. There’s a new department that sounds like a Yes Minister spoof with two billionaires in-charge. There’s Secretary of Homeland Security who shot her own dog and one guy who everyone confuses with an iconic rock band.
item.dc:creator: Nirmalya Dutta

item.title: 'Trump is targeting bottom line': Israel expects new US administration to take hard line on Iran
item.description: Israel anticipates the new Trump administration will take a tough stance against Iran, potentially paving the way for peace agreements with Arab nations. Energy Minister Eli Cohen expressed optimism that Trump's return could lead to a resolution in Lebanon, pushing Hezbollah away from the border, while emphasizing Israel's right to military action if necessary.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump fallout? CNN set to fire hundreds of employees after dismal ratings during election coverage
item.description: Over the years, Donald Trump has been relentless in his public criticisms of CNN, often using the network as a punching bag in his ongoing battle against mainstream media. He coined the term “fake news” largely in reference to CNN, frequently accusing the network of bias and suggesting that it was part of a “media conspiracy” against him and his supporters.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Eva Longoria says she is moving out of 'dystopian' US because Kamala Harris didn't win
item.description: “The shocking part is not that he won,” Longoria told Marie Claire in an interview for its November cover story conducted two days after Trump triumphed in the presidential race. “It’s that a convicted criminal who spews so much hate could hold the highest office,” Longoria explained and admitted her privilege that she could move to another country unlike most Americans.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Russian chef Alexei Zimin, known for anti-war stance, found dead in Belgrade apartment
item.description: Renowned Russian chef and vocal critic of the Ukraine war, Alexei Zimin, was found dead in his Belgrade apartment. Zimin, who had been residing in London, was visiting Serbia to promote his latest book. While the circumstances surrounding his death are not considered suspicious, an autopsy is scheduled.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Melania likes 'First Buddy' Elon Musk, Trump's inner circle feeling iced out
item.description: Elon Musk has become a close confidant of President-elect Donald Trump, frequently seen at Mar-a-Lago. This newfound friendship has reportedly shifted the dynamics within Trump's inner circle, with some old-timers feeling sidelined but First Lady to-be Melania Trump is approving of Elon Musk's proximity to her husband and she is believed to be a fan of the Tesla CEO.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: The Onion acquires Alex Jones' Infowars in bankruptcy auction
item.description: The Onion, a satirical publication, has successfully acquired Infowars, the website founded by conspiracy theorist Alex Jones, in a bankruptcy auction. The acquisition, supported by families of the Sandy Hook Elementary School shooting victims, aims to transform Infowars into a parody of itself, satirizing misinformation and online personalities.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: FBI raids Polymarket CEO Shayne Coplan's home days after platform accurately predicted Trump's win
item.description: The FBI searched the Manhattan apartment of Shayne Coplan, CEO of prediction market platform Polymarket, as part of an investigation into whether the platform operated as an unlicensed commodities exchange. The investigation centers around Polymarket's allowance of US users to place bets, potentially violating a previous settlement with the US government.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Greece in talks with Israel to develop 2 billion euro 'Iron Dome'
When Tulsi Gabbard clarified her nationality: 'I am not of Indian origin'
item.description: ​Tulsi Gabbard's mother Carol Porter Gabbard was raised in a multicultural household and became interested in Hinduism. All her children have Hindu names -- Bhakti, Jai, Aryan, Tulsi and Vrindavan. Tulsi also follows Hinduism. Old Videos of Tulsi chanting Hare Krishna are viral after she became the first Hindu to head US spy agencies.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
